## Terminal Configuration

### Linux (GNOME Terminal)
1. Open Terminal → Preferences
2. Select your profile → Text tab
3. Enable "Custom font"
4. Choose one of the installed Nerd Fonts

### Linux (Terminator)
1. Right-click → Preferences
2. Profiles → [Your Profile] → General
3. Uncheck "Use system fixed width font"
4. Select a Nerd Font from the dropdown

### macOS (Terminal.app)
1. Terminal → Preferences
2. Profiles → Text
3. Click "Font" and select a Nerd Font

### macOS (iTerm2)
1. iTerm2 → Preferences
2. Profiles → Text
3. Change Font to a Nerd Font

### Windows (Windows Terminal)
1. Open Windows Terminal
2. Settings (Ctrl+,)
3. Profiles → [Your Profile] → Appearance
4. Font face → Select a Nerd Font

